\chapter*{Chapter 1}

Summary: Sa\~{}njaya ({\dn sa~njaya}) tells King D.rtaraa.s.tra ({\dn
  d.rtaraa.s.tra}) what is happening on the battlefield, including a
conversation between Prince Arjuna ({\dn arjuna}) and Lord K.r.s.na
({\dn k.r.s.na}). Prince Arjuna sees relatives on the battlefield and
feels sadness.\\

The main characters are:

\begin{itemize}

\item Sa\~{}njaya is a secretary of King D.rtaraa.s.tra.

\item D.rtaraa.s.tra was the son of king, and he had a brother named
  Paa.n.du ({\dn paa.n.du}). D.rtaraa.s.tra was blind from birth, so
  Paa.n.du became king.

  Paa.n.du died, and his five sons, each called a Paa.n.dava ({\dn
    paa.n.dava}), became kings. The Paa.n.davas are the good guys.

  D.rtaraa.s.tra had one hundred sons. Duryodhana ({\dn duryodhana})
  was the oldest. He wanted to be king. He is a bad guy.

\item Prince Arjuna is one of the five Paa.n.davas.

\item Lord K.r.s.na (sometimes spelled ``Krishna'') is the eighth
  incarnation of Lord Vi.s.nu ({\dn vi.s.nu}) (sometimes spelled
  ``Vishnu''). He is an ally of Prince Arjuna.

  Vi.s.nu, Brahma ({\dn brahma}), and "Siva ({\dn "siva}) (sometimes
  spelled ``Shiva'') are the three major gods in Hinduism. Vi.s.nu is
  the preserver of the universe, Brahma is the creator of the
  universe, and "Siva is the destroyer of the universe.
\end{itemize}

